Color. Carapace (
Fig. 9
) yellow-brown, median part darker than other parts, and with thin annular brown patch around each seta. Each eye with a black ring. Chelicerae yellow. Endites yellow, black distally. Labium yellowbrown, gray distally. Sternum yellow-brown, with annular brown patch around each seta. Legs brown. Opisthosoma with scattered setae surround by annular brown patches; dorsum of opisthosoma covered by a dorsal scutum and with four dark brown muscle impressions centrally, the posterior part with two black lateral patches and a median black patch; laterally yellow-brown with a few large black patches; venter yellowish. Spinnerets yellowbrown.

Prosoma (
Fig. 9
). Carapace longer than wide, highest medially, head protruding forward and beyond clypeus, anterior margin with several black setae. Both eye rows recurved in dorsal view. Eye measurements: AME 0.09 , ALE 0.07 , PME 0.07 , PLE 0.07 ; AME – AME 0.08 , AME – ALE 0.02 , ALE – ALE 0.29 , PME – PME 0.05 , PME – PLE 0.05 , PLE – PLE 0.31 , ALE and PLE contiguous. MOA 0.13 long, anterior posterior 0.18 , back width 0.13 . Clypeus 0.21 high, with a few gray setae. Endites with gray scopulae. Labium 0.08 long, 0.13 wide. Sternum 0.36 long, 0.36 wide, with scattered short black setae.

Opisthosoma (
Fig. 9
). Oval, longer than wide, with scattered short black setae.

Color (
Fig. 12
). Opisthosoma yellow-brown, without dorsal scutum; anterior part with two pairs of dark brown muscle impressions, and posterior part with an inverted V-shaped marking.
